00:03:13.899 --> 00:03:15.000
We win!

00:03:19.633 --> 00:03:22.100
So in these assignments
we have learned how to

00:03:22.100 --> 00:03:25.066
create new GameObjects,
how to position them in the Scene,

00:03:25.233 --> 00:03:28.666
add new components to them,
write our own custom behaviors

00:03:28.666 --> 00:03:30.166
for them using simple scripting.

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:34.666
We've seen how to use lights, cameras,
Colliders, Triggers, Rigidbodies.

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.100
We can collect and count objects.

00:03:37.266 --> 00:03:40.500
Though this is a very simple example,
it covers a large set

00:03:40.533 --> 00:03:44.266
of basic subjects important to
understanding how to use Unity.

00:03:45.333 --> 00:03:48.200
For continued learning about
Unity, check the Learn site

00:03:48.366 --> 00:03:51.033
for more lessons,
assignments and projects.

